title: Frank Zappa - FZ:OZ (2002) 2CD (Sydney, Australia, 1976)
description:
FZ:OZ (pronounced "eff-zee oh-zee"; in imitation of "Aussie") is a live album, released in 2002, containing almost all of a January 20, 1976 concert at the Hordern Pavilion in Sydney, Australia.

Much of the featured material had not been released at the time of the recording, including "Canard Toujours", which later became "Kreega Bondola", then later changed to "Let's Move to Cleveland", which was included on Does Humor Belong in Music? (1986) and several tracks that would later appear on Zoot Allures (1976). One song, "Kaiser Rolls", appears for the first time on FZ:OZ.

This particular band - with tenor saxophonist Napoleon Murphy Brock, bassist Roy Estrada, drummer Terry Bozzio, and keyboardist Andre Lewis (in his only tour with Zappa) - has only been represented sporadically on Zappa's earlier releases.

Zappa's guitar solos are of the usual high caliber, and his band is well rehearsed.



Frank Zappa

FZ:OZ

(Hordern Pavilion, Sydney, Australia, January 20, 1976)

2002
